**How to Create A VPC with Public and Private Subnets AND IGW and Route Tables**

1- Login to the AWS Console  
2- Go to VPC Section   
3- Click on Create VPC

![][image1]

4-Give VPC Name and Give VPC CIDR Range 10.1.0.0/16

![][image2]  
5-Click on Create VPC  
6-Click On Actions in VPC  
7-Select the Edit VPC settings   
![][image3]  
8-Check the Enable DNS Hostname

![][image4]  
![][image5]

9-Click on Save  
10-Click on Create Subnets   
![][image6]  
11-Select VPC   
![][image7]  
12-Give Subnet Name and IP range  
![][image8]  
13-Like You can create how many you want I am, taking here 6 Subnets 

![][image9]  
   
14-Click on Create Internet Gateway

![][image10]

15-Attach the IGW to VPC

![][image11]

16-Click on Create Internet Gateway

![][image12]

17-Here I am Taking 3 Route Tables VPC-1-Public and VPC-1-Private and VPC-1-DB 

![][image13]

18-Click on VPC-1-Public click on Edit subnet associations

![][image14]

19-Add your public subnets VPC-1-public-1 and VPC-1-Public-2

![][image15]

20-Like add Remaing two tables add private into private subnets and DB into DB subnets 

21-Select the VPC-1-Public  select the click on route add intent gateway

![][image16]  
![][image17]

21-Create Two Nat-Gateways 

![][image18]

22-Like one more Create 

![][image19]

23-Click on VPC-1-Private Seletc the Route add NAt-Gateway Private-Subnet-NAT  
![][image20]

![][image21]

23-Like VPC-1-DB click on Route add DB-Subnet-NAT

![][image22]

![][image23]

Now you can see the Full VPC Diagram

![][image24]

If you want Public IP whenever you want to launch the server you can select the subnets do this 

![][image25]
